You need to clarify but the problem is, but as @Hybrid_Piper mentioned the if/else conditions would cause an error. You cannot have the same conditions for an if and an else if. I assume that you are trying to make it so if you click button 2 it will switch the direction of air flow in the solenoid. What you should do is remove the else if, and then in the original if you can use a ternary operator to set the air flow to toggle.

Something like:
if (m_leftStick.getRawButton(2)) {
doubleSolenoid.set(doubleSolenoid.get() ? Value.kReverse : Value.kForward);
} else {
doubleSolenoid.set(Value.kOff);
}
